<a href="#0" id="0">Being clear and precise about the form of behaviour we care about even in this simple case will also help clarify what it means for the science of AI to be successful.</a>
<a href="#1" id="1">As we will see, however, there will be good reasons to move to answering questions of a more restricted form.</a>
<a href="#2" id="2">We want to understand what it takes to produce the intelligent behaviour that people exhibit.</a>
<a href="#3" id="3">So the question really needs to be more like this: What kind of system would have the necessary background knowledge to be able to behave the way people do?</a>
<a href="#4" id="4">So to account for what people are actually able to do, we need to consider what it would take to have a system that knows a lot about its world and can apply that knowledge as needed, the way people can.</a>
